This paper is about evolutionary deep intelligence and the synthesis of efficient deep neural network models. The most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper focuses on the use of evolutionary algorithms to generate neural network architectures. The second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks. The third most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the paper mentions the potential applications of the synthesized networks in computer vision tasks. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms for generating intelligent systems. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper mentions the potential applications of the synthesized networks in control systems.
